author: Todd S. Purdum
title: AFSCME endorses Clinton
text:
The American Federation of State, County and Municipal Employees endorsed Hillary Clinton for president. The union said in a statement that its 35-member executive board voted “overwhelmingly” to back Clinton Friday.
AFSCME President Lee Saunders said “members want the candidate who will be the most effective champion for working families, and who will be able to deliver a victory in this critically important election. AFSCME members believe that candidate is Hillary Clinton."
The 1.3 million member union was expected to endorse Clinton.
